result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (6th) and Operating w/ PAC (6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Jacob J Brunow was found guilty of OWI (6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court finds the defendant eligible for the Substance Abuse Program after serving 12 months of confinement.

superMiscConds.notes: Bond amount posted shall be applied.  Court enters judgment for any current unpaid financial obligation.  Outstanding financial obligations shall be paid from all prison wages at a rate of 25% and the balance due as a condition of extended supervision.  If extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with financial obligations owing, a judgment shall be entered.
Defendant shall obtain and maintain full time employment or schooling or combination thereof to be full time.

Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol or controlled substance without a valid prescription and then take medication as prescribed.  

Defendant shall not enter any bars, taverns, liquor stores, or establishment where primary purpose is sale or service of alcohol.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent and comply with treatment recommendations.  Agent shall determine if a psychological assessment is necessary.  

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample.

Defendant shall pay any supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.

Defendant shall notify his agent of any prescription medications within 24 hours of receiving the prescription.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and safety plan.

supervisions.notes: Effective upon licensure.  Attached is an information sheet for the defendant regarding installation.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and safety plan.
